Customized Function Keys
------------------------

  <F2> - Help Screen (this screen message)
  <F3> - Write
  <F5> - Search and Replace
  <F7> - Buffer


Navigation
----------
  
  ctrl-o  - Jump back
  ctrl-i  - Jump forward
  nG......- move to the end of the current file
  0	  - move to the beginning of the current line (number zero)
  $.......- move to the end of the current line
  w	  - move forward count word(s)
  b.......- move backward count word(s)
  G	  - move to the end of the current file
  (.......- count sentences back
  )	  - count sentences forward
  {.......- count paragraphs back
  }	  - count paragraphs forward


Operations
----------
  
  ctrl-n  - Word completion 
  ctrl-w  - Erases word
  cc - change
  dd - delete
  yy - yank into register
  / - search (use n to continue into file)

//use d3w to delete the next 3 words


Saving and Reading Files
------------------------

  :r filename <return>	      - 
  :w			      - 
  :w newfile <return>	      - writes working file into newfile
  :12, 35w smallfile <return> -	writes lines 12-35 into new smallfile
  :w! prevfile <return>	      - write current file over an old file === prevfile


Text Selection
--------------

  V       -  selects entire lines 
  v       -  selects range of text
  ctrl-v  -  selects columns
  gv      -  reselect block


Configuration
-------------

  ~/.exrc	    - edit to implement vi configuration
  ~/.vi_help	    - edit THIS FILE
  :! "command"	    - enters command as if from terminal
  <ctrl-v><ctrl-m>  - creates return after :! "command"
